This page is all about me, and what I enjoy doing

A creative and competitive professional with a Bachelors degree majoring in English Literature and Classical studies. Experience working in customer service, social media and operational roles within internationally recognised companies. Confident working under pressure with a diverse team and able to self manage, de-escalate difficult situations and remain flexible and alert while smashing any targets. Download my CV

You may be wondering what on earth is this perfectly animated sun doing bobbing up and down this vector city, stuck in a never-ending loop of day and night? Well you see, this animation was one of the first things I was tasked with doing as part of learning to code. I seriously considered removing it from this page. I mean, it doesn't really add too much. However, every time I watch this little celestial body rise and fall, I am reminded how far I have come from late 2022, when I started coding. It also makes me laugh, as in the first drafts of the animation, the sun was all over the place, going on absolutely random tangents and then cannoning back the other way. The videos I sent to my friends showing this continue to be a source of laughter for us and act as a cornerstone for anyone who asks about my progress in my course and in coding in general. So, for now, my little Errant Sun shall continue to do laps of the sky and I hope he brings you as much simplistic joy as he brings me.
